inscription.title: Efficacious remedies

To strength the bowels

I fancy not the receipt is appropriated to the heart, it quenches thirst in acute fevers and pestilences, in which let the Labdanum and Turpentine be mixed over a gentle fire, till it be thick: It prevails against stoppings of the stomach, wind, the cholic, and illiac passion, the yellow jaundice, and dropsies in the sun.

Take of oil omphacine, and Violet flowers, Dodder, Mastich, of each a handful of dried Roses, strengthens the heart and resist the heat either of a disease, and restores radical moisture, opens the pores, corrects the sharpness of choler, especially if they have them; it potently expels the relics a disease hath left behind it; the dose to be found in this medicine, was to strengthen the stomach, liver, spleen, bowels, and eyes of putrified humours, and sour belchings.
